German Air Passengers Get Arbitration Board, Tagesspiegel Says

-- B y   A l e x   W e b b
-- 
2011-08-16T06:40:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-16/german-air-passengers-get-arbitration-board-tagesspiegel-says.html
German air passengers will be
represented by an arbitration board,  Tagesspiegel  reported,
citing Eva-Maria McCormack, a spokeswoman for  Bundesverband der
Deutschen Luftverkehrswirtschaft , the industry body that
represents German airlines.  It remains to be seen what role the existing arbitration
board for public transport will take in issues concerning  air
travel , the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Webb in Frankfurt 
 awebb25@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chad Thomas at   cthomas16@bloomberg.net . 